symbols.name: ui_button
symbols.description: Creates a button in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_file_selector
symbols.description: Creates a file selector in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_label
symbols.description: Creates a text or image label in the performance view.

initializerArguments.name: $grid_width
initializerArguments.description: The width of the label in grid units (1 to 6)

initializerArguments.name: $grid_height
initializerArguments.description: The height of the label in grid units (1 to 16)

symbols.name: ui_knob
symbols.description: Creates a knob in the performance view.

initializerArguments.name: $min
initializerArguments.description: The minimum value of the knob.

initializerArguments.name: $max
initializerArguments.description: The maximum value of the knob.

initializerArguments.name: $display_ratio
initializerArguments.description: The knob value is divided by <display-ratio> for display purposes.

symbols.name: ui_level_meter
symbols.description: Creates a level meter in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_menu
symbols.description: Creates a drop-down menu in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_mouse_area
symbols.description: Creates a mouse area in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_panel
symbols.description: Creates a panel for grouping widgets in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_slider
symbols.description: Creates a slider in the performance view.

initializerArguments.name: $min
initializerArguments.description: The minimum value of the slider.

initializerArguments.name: $max
initializerArguments.description: The maximum value of the slider.

symbols.name: ui_switch
symbols.description: Creates a switch in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_table
symbols.description: Creates a table in the performance view.

initializerArguments.name: $width
initializerArguments.description: The width of the table in grid units (1 ... 6).

initializerArguments.name: $height
initializerArguments.description: The height of the table in grid units (1 ... 16).

initializerArguments.name: $range
initializerArguments.description: The range of the table. If negative values are used, a bipolar table is created.

symbols.name: ui_text_edit
symbols.description: Creates a text edit field in the performance view.

symbols.name: ui_value_edit
symbols.description: Creates a value edit field (number box) in the performance view.

initializerArguments.name: $min
initializerArguments.description: The minimum value of the value edit.

initializerArguments.name: $max
initializerArguments.description: The maximum value of the value edit.

initializerArguments.name: $display_ratio
initializerArguments.description: The value is divided by <display-ratio> for display purposes.

symbols.name: ui_waveform
symbols.description: Creates a waveform display for displaying samples and optionally their slices. This widget can also be used to control specific parameters per slice and for MIDI drag and drop functionality.

initializerArguments.name: $width
initializerArguments.description: The width of the waveform in grid units (1 ... 6).

initializerArguments.name: $height
initializerArguments.description: The height of the waveform in grid units (1 ... 16).

symbols.name: ui_wavetable
symbols.description: Creates a wavetable display in the performance view, visualizing the state of a zone which is used as a wavetable.

symbols.name: ui_xy
symbols.description: Creates an XY pad in the performance view.
